Holding down B button when powering on will enter
System Control mode. The RGB LED will light blue,
continue to hold B button. Pressing the UP button
turns the sound on, the RGB LED flashes green once
to confirm this action. Pressing the DOWN button
mutes the sound and the RGB LED flashes red once
to indicate the result. Releasing B button will exit
System Control mode and the sketch will continue.

Holding down UP button when powering on puts the Arduboy in flashlight mode. This
fully turns on the RGB LED and illuminates all the pixels on the screen, resulting in a
bright white light suitable as a small flashlight. To exit flashlight mode, the Arduboy
must be restarted.
